Day 82 Summary – Road to Fluent Spanish
Today marked Day 82 of Road to Fluent Spanish. The lesson began with the daily Duolingo review, followed by new vocabulary and phrases from Memrise. This week’s 10 Key Weekly Conversational Phrases, both bonus phrases, and the weekly challenge phrase were reviewed extensively and reinforced through multiple quiz rounds.

The remainder of today’s work focused on Pimsleur Unit 3, Lesson 4 (review day). The lesson covered restaurant vocabulary, recommendations, buying and selling, describing work, discussing technology companies, French language vocabulary, and conversational phrases related to learning languages. Key vocabulary included phrases such as asking for recommendations, describing jobs, talking about studying French, buying and selling wine, and discussing where someone learned a language.

Throughout today’s review, several older conversational phrases from previous weeks were intentionally mixed in to reinforce long-term retention. Topics included introducing yourself, discussing work, asking for directions, restaurant conversations, ordering food and drinks, talking about free time, and everyday travel conversations. Continued emphasis was placed on correcting recurring grammar mistakes, particularly:

trabajo para (not trabajo por)
corregirme and cometo errores
me gusta + infinitive
Complete conversational responses instead of one-word answers.
By the end of today’s review, most of the material from this week’s conversational phrases and Pimsleur review was being recalled automatically with only minor corrections needed. The remaining weaknesses are primarily conversational grammar and natural sentence formation rather than vocabulary recall.

